data.title: Watch: Hyeri, Park Se Wan, Jo Aram And More Shine As Vibrant Cheerleaders In Upcoming Youth Film "Victory"

data.text:
The upcoming youth movie “Victory” has released a teaser poster!

Directed by Park Beom Soo, “Victory” is a youth film starring Hyeri, Park Se Wan, Lee Jung Ha, Jo Aram and others. The film depicts the story of Geoje Commercial High School’s cheerleading team Millennium Girls, where eight team members with unique personalities are gathered. Set in the backdrop of 1999, “Victory” follows the passionate story of best friends Pil Seon (Hyeri) and Mi Na (Park Se Wan) as they put together a cheerleading team in order to be able to dance.

The newly released teaser poster grabs attention as nine characters leap energetically over the blue sea, emitting a refreshing vibe akin to a breath of fresh air.

Sporting cheerleading poms, the squad ascends into the sky, each displaying their distinct personalities and embodying the mantra “Stand Up! Tension Up! Cheer Up!” The vibrant imagery and dynamic depiction of the cheerleading club, brimming with passion and energy, heighten anticipation for “Victory.”

Also check out the teaser showcasing the Millennium Girls team up and perform below!

“Victory” is set to premiere on August 14. Stay tuned!

In the meantime, check out Hyeri in “My Roommate is a Gumiho” below:
